### 5. src/types.ts (Type Definitions)

**Location:** `/extensions/{plugin-id}/src/types.ts`

**Purpose:** Defines configuration types, account types, and protocol-specific types.

**Key Components:**

**A. Account Configuration Type:**
```typescript
export type {PluginName}AccountConfig = {
  enabled?: boolean;
  name?: string;
  // Protocol-specific fields
  // e.g., IRC: host, port, nick, tls, nickserv
  // e.g., Nostr: privateKey, relays, profile

  // Security/routing
  dmPolicy?: DmPolicy;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  defaultTo?: string;

  // Group configs (if supporting groups)
  groupPolicy?: GroupPolicy;
  groupAllowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  groups?: Record<string, {PluginName}ChannelConfig>;

  // Markdown/chunking
  markdown?: MarkdownConfig;
  historyLimit?: number;
  textChunkLimit?: number;
  blockStreaming?: boolean;
};
```

**B. Resolved Account Type:**
```typescript
export interface Resolved{PluginName}Account {
  accountId: string;
  name?: string;
  enabled: boolean;
  configured: boolean;
  // Processed/validated fields
  config: {PluginName}AccountConfig;
}
```

**C. Top-level Config Type:**
